<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM28150 - Approval of SIPs: Applying for approval</h1>
  <p>There is no prescribed application form, however there is an informal review 
    document (<a href="essum29700.htm">checklist</a>) that can be used to demonstrate 
    that the legislation governing approved SIPs is satisfied (see <a href="ESSUM29700.htm">ESSUM29700</a>). 
    Applications should be supported by whatever evidence an officer of HM Revenue 
    &amp; Customs requires (paragraph 1). The documentary evidence generally required 
    is set out on the front page of the checklist.</p>
<p>Applications for approval can be made by any body corporate (UK resident or otherwise) which has established a SIP. Guidance on establishing schemes is at <a href="ESSUM28250.htm">ESSUM28250</a>.</p>
<p>Foreign companies may wish to establish a SIP for employees of their UK subsidiary companies. Whilst it will be rare for a foreign scheme to satisfy the requirements of Schedule 2 without modification, it may be possible for</p>
<ul>
<li>the subsidiary company or companies to set up free-standing SIPs which fully satisfy Schedule 2,  or</li>
<li>an addendum to be made to the parent companyâ€™s foreign scheme, to disapply the unacceptable features of the foreign scheme and to import the rules which are required to satisfy Schedule 2 (see <a href="ESSUM20100.htm">ESSUM20100</a>).</li>
</ul>
<p>Before submitting a SIP for formal approval the company may provide draft documents in order that ESSU can review all plan documentation to ensure that it is in a form capable of approval (see <a href="ESSUM11100.htm">ESSUM11100</a>). Once this preliminary review is completed ESSU will advise of any changes needed and in due course advise when the plan is in a form capable of approval. It is at this point that the SIP should be formally adopted by the company and application made for formal approval. Invitations to participate should not be issued until the SIP has formal approval and until such time as the relevant agreement (for partnership shares or free shares, as appropriate) and any invitation material have also been reviewed by ESSU (see <a href="ESSUM28250.htm">ESSUM28250</a>).</p>
